  "text": "This analysis identifies the Kubernetes v1beta1 to v1 API storage version registration system. The key components are:\n\n1. **REST Storage Providers** (in pkg/registry/): These files define both v1beta1Storage() and v1Storage() methods for different API groups:\n   - admissionregistration/rest/storage_apiserver.go: Registers both v1 and v1beta1 storage for validatingadmissionpolicies and related resources\n   - authentication/rest/storage_authentication.go: Provides v1beta1 and v1 storage for selfsubjectreviews\n   - storage/rest/storage_storage.go: Manages v1beta1 and v1 storage for volumeattributesclasses\n   - resource/rest/storage_resource.go: Provides v1beta1 storage for resource group items (deviceclasses, resourceclaims, etc.)\n\n2. **StorageVersion Manager Interface** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storageversion/manager.go):\n   - Defines the Manager interface for recording and updating storage versions\n   - Maintains ResourceInfo structs with EncodingVersion and DirectlyDecodableVersions\n   - Handles update status tracking for each GroupResource\n\n3. **ResourceEncodingConfig** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go):\n   - Interface that controls which GroupVersion is used for etcd storage via StorageEncodingFor()\n   - DefaultResourceEncodingConfig implementation stores resource-specific encodings\n   - SetResourceEncoding() method configures external and internal encoding versions for resources\n\n4. **Storage Factory Configuration** (pkg/kubeapiserver/default_storage_factory_builder.go):\n   - NewStorageFactoryConfig() initializes ResourceEncodingOverrides array\n   - Defines which resources store in which versions (e.g., volumeattributesclasses in v1beta1)\n   - These overrides are merged using MergeResourceEncodingConfigs()\n\n5. **Configuration Merging** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/resourceconfig/helpers.go):\n   - MergeResourceEncodingConfigs() applies per-resource storage version overrides\n   - Sets up the mapping of GroupVersionResources to their storage versions\n\n6. **Aggregator Configuration** (pkg/controlplane/apiserver/aggregator.go):\n   - Sets up EncodeVersioner using runtime.NewMultiGroupVersioner\n   - Maps v1 and v1beta1 versions for aggregator and API extension storage\n   - Defines which version is prioritized for etcd encoding\n\n7. **API Version Priorities** (cmd/kube-apiserver/app/aggregator.go):\n   - Defines priority ordering for different API versions (e.g., storage.k8s.io v1 has priority 15, v1beta1 has priority 9)\n   - Ensures consistent version ordering across API groups"
